  "prompt": "What percentage of freshers are accepted into the IIM's every year?",
  "response": "The acceptance rate for freshers applying to the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) varies from year to year and depends on several factors, including the number of applicants, the number of available seats, and the specific IIM in question, as each IIM has different admission criteria and capacities.\n\nGenerally, the acceptance rate for IIMs is quite low. For example, in recent years, the acceptance rate has often been around 1-3% for the prestigious IIMs like IIM Ahmedabad, IIM Bangalore, and IIM Calcutta. This means that out of thousands of applicants, only a small percentage are selected for admission.\n\nFor precise and updated figures, you would need to check the specific admission statistics released by the IIMs or consult their official websites or annual reports.",
